  "texts": [
    "According to the rubric, the resolved scores are calculated as the sum of the two human scores for items 1, 7, and 8.",
    "It is worth noting that the stimuli were very long and including the stimuli in addition to the full rubric would have exceeded the context limits we imposed for practical considerations.",
    "Secondly, in the case that the resolved score was the addition of the trait scores for each rater, the rubric described only the rater score, not the resolved score.",
    "So we employed a language model to summarize the differences between a high and low-scoring essay.",
    "Perhaps managing this better could lead to more constructive feedback."
